---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Lexicon | Grithos"
  description="The language of Grithos ‚Äî key terms defined. From Grithosian to Forge Day, every word carries weight. Learn the vocabulary of a philosophy built on grit and ethos."
  ogTitle="The Lexicon ‚Äî Grithos"
  ogDescription="The language of Grithos defined. Every word carries weight. Learn the vocabulary of a philosophy built on grit and ethos."
  ogUrl="https://grithos.com/lexicon"
  canonical="https://grithos.com/lexicon"
  activePage="lexicon"
>

<style is:inline>
  /* ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê PAGE HERO ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 40px;
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 40%; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 800px; height: 800px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(196,168,130,.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .page-hero .wrap { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .page-hero-overline {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .page-hero-title {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 52px);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .page-hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 18px);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê LEXICON ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê */
  .lexicon-section {
    padding: 0 0 120px;
  }
  .lexicon-list {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .lexicon-item {
    background: var(--card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    transition: all .3s;
  }
  .lexicon-item:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold-border);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  .lexicon-term {
    font-family: var(--heading);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.5vw, 26px);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .lexicon-pronunciation {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--gold);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .lexicon-def {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.85;
  }
  .lexicon-def em {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 14px;
    display: block;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }
  .lexicon-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    background: var(--gold-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--gold-border);
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  /* ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê CLOSING ‚ïê‚ïê‚ïê */
  .closing {
    padding: 0 0 120px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .closing-divider {
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 80px;
  }
  .closing-text {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.8vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto 20px;
  }
  .closing-sub {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 18px);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 480px;
    margin: 0 auto 40px;
  }
  .back-link {
    font-family: var(--body);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    transition: color .2s;
  }
  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }
  .back-link svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; }
</style>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <img src="/assets/images/grithos-logo.png" alt="Grithos" style="width: 120px; height: auto; margin-bottom: 16px; opacity: 0.85;">
    <p class="page-hero-overline reveal d1">The Language</p>
    <h1 class="page-hero-title reveal d2">The Lexicon</h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub reveal d3">Every philosophy has its language. These are the words that carry weight in Grithos.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LEXICON -->
<section class="lexicon-section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="lexicon-list">

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Grithos</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/Àà…°r…™Œ∏.…ís/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">A philosophy of life built on grit and ethos. The fusion of relentless endurance and moral character. Not a religion. Not a movement. A way of living.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Grithosian</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/…°r…™ÀàŒ∏o ä.zi.…ôn/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">A person who lives by the philosophy of Grithos. Not someone who merely studies it ‚Äî someone who practices it. Daily. A Grithosian tells the truth, keeps their word, owns what is theirs, and builds what lasts.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Five Pillars</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Structure</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The foundational categories of Grithos: <strong>Virtue, Apex, Control, Death,</strong> and <strong>Verity.</strong> Every tenet, every practice, every decision filters through one of these five pillars.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d4">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Fifteen Tenets</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Structure</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">Fifteen rules of life ‚Äî three under each pillar. They are not suggestions. They are the operating instructions for a Grithosian life. Memorized. Practiced. Lived.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Creed</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Foundation</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The central declaration of Grithos. Five lines. No filler. It defines what a Grithosian believes about truth, strength, ownership, mortality, and legacy.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Bounds</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ba ändz/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The natural laws, limits, and structures that govern reality. Gravity. Time. Consequence. A Grithosian does not fight the bounds ‚Äî a Grithosian trusts them, works within them, and builds accordingly. <em>"Trust the Bounds." ‚Äî Tenet IX</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Architects</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">Heritage</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">Sixty-two figures across five pillars whose lives embodied the principles of Grithos before it had a name. Emperors, slaves, warriors, engineers, and rebels ‚Äî not founders, but proof that these ideas have always existed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Verity</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/Ààv…õr.…™.ti/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The Fifth Pillar. Truth in the engineered age. A Grithosian confronts the algorithms, the systems, and the comfort machines with eyes open. Verity is not paranoia ‚Äî it is informed awareness. Master the tools. Never serve them. <em>"Walk Forward. Eyes Open." ‚Äî Tenet XV</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d4">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Forge Day</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">March 13</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The founding date of Grithos ‚Äî Friday the 13th. A day the superstitious fear. A day Grithos was forged in. On Forge Day, do one thing that is hard on purpose. Every year. No exceptions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Daily Practice</h2>
        <span class="lexicon-tag">365 Days</span>
        <p class="lexicon-def">One practice per day, every day of the year. Each tied to a tenet. Each tied to a pillar. Philosophy without practice is just talk. The Daily Practice is where talk ends and Grithos begins.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Redirect</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ÀåriÀê.d…™Ààr…õkt/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The act of immediately pivoting when something fails, falls through, or changes. No spiraling. No stewing. No standing at closed doors. Something broke? Redirect. Now. <em>"Redirect Immediately." ‚Äî Tenet VIII</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d3">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Own It</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The Grithos posture toward everything ‚Äî results, failures, decisions, and outcomes. A Grithosian does not blame. A Grithosian does not deflect. Whatever happened, own your piece of it. Then move.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d4">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Mark</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The legacy a Grithosian leaves behind. Not fame. Not wealth. The mark ‚Äî the evidence that you lived with purpose, built something that outlasted you, and left the world different because you were in it. <em>"Not a scratch ‚Äî a mark." ‚Äî Tenet XII</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d1">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Grit</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/…°r…™t/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The half of Grithos that endures. Relentless persistence. The refusal to quit when it gets hard. Not stubbornness ‚Äî directed force. Grit without ethos is just aggression. Together, they become Grithos.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-item reveal d2">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Ethos</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/ÀàiÀê.Œ∏…ís/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The half of Grithos that guides. Moral character. The internal compass that says do right ‚Äî even when it costs you. Ethos without grit is just philosophy. Together, they become Grithos.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-entry reveal">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Apex</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-pronunciation">/Ààe…™.p…õks/</p>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The highest expression of human capability. Not arrogance ‚Äî fact. A Grithosian does not shrink from strength. Apex is the recognition that you are the most capable species on earth, and that capability carries the greatest accountability. <em>"Never Shrink. Never Apologize for Strength." ‚Äî Tenet IV</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-entry reveal">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Footing</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">Where philosophy meets the ground you‚Äôre standing on. The Footing takes real situations ‚Äî grief, failure, conflict, fear ‚Äî and shows how each pillar responds. Not theory. Practice. Start here when life hits and you need Grithos to hit back.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-entry reveal">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">Build With</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The Verity stance toward technology. Use the tool. Direct the output. Own the decisions. A Grithosian builds with AI as a partner, not a master. The moment you serve the tool, you have surrendered your apex nature. <em>"Build With. Never Build Under." ‚Äî Tenet XIV</em></p>
      </div>

      <div class="lexicon-entry reveal">
        <h2 class="lexicon-term">The Engineered Age</h2>
        <p class="lexicon-def">The era we live in now. Algorithms shape your thoughts, machines predict your behavior, and comfort is manufactured at scale. Verity exists because of the Engineered Age ‚Äî and a Grithosian does not sleep through it.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CLOSING -->
<section class="closing">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="closing-divider"></div>
    <p class="closing-text reveal d1">Learn the language. Live the philosophy.</p>
    <p class="closing-sub reveal d2">Words without action are just noise.</p>
    <div class="reveal d3">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10.5 19.5 3 12m0 0 7.5-7.5M3 12h18" /></svg>
        Back to Grithos
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
